    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="540"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Raikes</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Hay</hi>: I have informed Lord Lansdowne by
                    telegraph of the offer which the President has made to send home the remains of
                    Lord Pauncefote in a vessel of the American Navy as a testimony of respect, and
                    I have asked him whether I may accept his offer on benalf of Lady
                    Pauncefote.</p>
                <p>Yours, very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur S. Raikes.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
